tibackup (0.9.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Web UI extensions:
    - File browser can now create folders: a "New folder" action in the path
      picker, backed by POST /api/mkdir (local roots, same confinement as
      /api/browse) and POST /api/ssh/<uuid>/mkdir (remote SSH targets).
    - Logs tab: a new "rsync logs" card exposes the per-job raw rsync --log-file
      output (GET /api/logs/rsync and /api/logs/rsync/<job>/<file>).
    - Logs tab: running jobs are highlighted, and a running job's run log can be
      watched live — GET /api/logs/runs/<file>?offset=N returns an incremental
      tail that the run-log viewer polls while the job runs.
    - Settings: a "Send test mail" button (POST /api/prefs/test-mail) verifies the
      SMTP settings over the same transport as backup notifications; it can test
      unsaved form values and honours the write-only password (blank = stored).
  * Fix: the backup target is unmounted again after a successful run. A guard added
    during earlier hardening (Prio-2) only unmounted drives tiBackup had mounted
    itself, so a target already mounted at job start (e.g. auto-mounted by the OS on
    insertion) was left mounted. Now controlled by a per-job "Unmount drive after
    backup" option (default on), which unmounts regardless of who mounted the drive.

 -- Rene Hadler <rene@hadler.me>  Fri, 17 Jul 2026 14:30:00 +0200

tibackup (0.9.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Prio-3 hardening batch:
    - Scheduler rewritten to strict-slot firing backed by a persisted per-job
      last-run sidecar (/etc/tibackup/scheduler_state.conf): a slot fires at most
      once (no more double-firing on restart or fast completion) and a slot
      missed while the daemon was down is skipped, not resurrected.
    - systemd unit: conservative sandboxing that does not break mount/LUKS/sudo/
      /mnt visibility (ProtectSystem=true, ProtectKernelTunables/Logs,
      ProtectControlGroups, ProtectClock/Hostname, RestrictRealtime,
      LockPersonality, UMask=0077, TimeoutStopSec, Type).
    - Logs moved from /etc/tibackup/logs to /var/log/tibackup (FHS). The postinst
      migrates existing logs; paths/logs is rewritten on upgrade. logrotate
      (copytruncate) rotates the held-open tibackup.log; a tmpfiles.d rule
      age-cleans the write-once run/rsync logs.
    - SMTP password is now write-only over the API (never returned to the
      browser); the notification From address is configurable (smtp/from).
    - Session cookie Max-Age is coupled to web/session_ttl.
    - Content-Security-Policy is now sent as a real HTTP header so frame-ancestors
      is enforced (it is ignored in a <meta> tag).
    - Removed dead DiskWatcher finished()/error() signals and connects.

 -- Rene Hadler <rene@hadler.me>  Fri, 17 Jul 2026 09:00:00 +0200

tibackup (0.8.3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix postinst syntax error that aborted package configuration ("word
    unexpected (expecting ;;)"). The maintainer script comment contained a
    literal #DEBHELPER# token, which dh_installdeb expanded inline into the
    middle of the configure) case branch, corrupting the script. Reworded the
    comment so the token only appears on its own line.

 -- Rene Hadler <rene@hadler.me>  Thu, 16 Jul 2026 13:00:00 +0200

