tibackup (0.8.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add SSH-Server backups: pull directories from remote Linux servers via
    rsync over SSH onto the backup disk. Public-key auth only, pinned host
    keys, remote file browser for picking source folders; multiple SSH servers
    can be combined in a single job.
  * Add rsync and openssh-client dependencies.
  * Requires tibackuplib >= 0.8.2.

 -- Rene Hadler <rene@hadler.me>  Thu, 16 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

tibackup (0.8.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Web UI now serves HTTPS by default (Proxmox-style): a self-signed TLS
    certificate is generated on install at /etc/tibackup/pki/tibackup-web.{pem,key}
    and used automatically. Regenerate with `tiBackup --regenerate-web-cert`.
  * Fresh installs bind the web UI to all interfaces (0.0.0.0); existing installs
    keep their configured bind on upgrade. Override via web/tls_cert, web/tls_key
    and web/bind in /etc/tibackup/main.conf.
  * Add openssl dependency (used to generate the web certificate).

 -- Rene Hadler <rene@hadler.me>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

